parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the fuel tank selector valve can cause fuel to overflow from one tank to another, leading to fuel spills, leaks, and potential fires, which can pose a significant safety risk to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Fuel spills or leaks from the fuel tank filler cap
fuel pumps from one tank to another
fuel gauge erratic or drops to zero
fuel smell inside the vehicle
fuel gushes out when the fuel cap is released
and fuel spills onto the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause a fire, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The alternator catches on fire
smoke comes out of the hood
the vehicle is unable to start
the battery is drained
the electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause a fire, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The ignition switch shorts out
the vehicle catches on fire
the interior of the vehicle is burned
the ignition switch fails to start the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a fire, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The wiring harness melts
the fuse box melts
the vehicle catches on fire
smoke comes out of the hood
the electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manufacturer to properly repair recalled vehicles can lead to accidents, injuries, or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle catches on fire after recall repair
the recall repair does not fix the issue
the vehicle is still experiencing problems after recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Complete brake failure on long grades can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake failure
especially on long descents
requiring the use of low gear and occasional use of the parking brake to control speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Overheating of brake system components can lead to premature wear, damage, and failure, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Front brakes engaging continuously
overheating of calipers
pads
and rotors
damaging the brake system.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: ABS Malfunction in Humid or Rainy Weather
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS malfunction can cause the rear wheels to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: ABS working in the opposite way of its design
causing rear wheels to lock up when brakes are lightly applied
especially in humid or rainy weather conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake line failure can cause sudden loss of brake function, leading to accidents and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal going to the floor with no warning
rupture of metallic brake lines at bend locations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS failure can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: ABS warning light coming on and off
failure of the ABS system
causing rear wheels to lock up
and continued braking even after releasing the brake pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and brake pedal stiffness can cause difficulty in shifting gears and braking, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Clutch and brake pedal becoming stiff
making it hard to shift gears and brake.
